title: Le Chef
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Middle Eastern, Lebanese, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. A small Lebanese cafe with a more affordable menu than the restaurants surrounding it. Plenty for vegans, such as lentil and lemon soup; hummus and baba ghanoush with flatbread; foule; chips; side plates of sweet onions, pickles, and mint leaves; green beans in a tomato sauce; and fried cauliflower with tahini. Frequented by both tourists and locals.
